ratio = 0.8 # bootstrapping ratio
n = round(1643*ratio, 0) # nrow
k = 9 # number of input variables

bootstrapping_mse <- list()
bootstrapping_adj_r2 <- list()
bootstrapping_sum_rbc <- list()
temporary_df_list <- list()
for(i in 1: 100) {
  set.seed(i)
  temporary_df_list[[i]] <- combined_result1 %>%
    sample_n(n) %>% # bootstraping
    mutate(mean_true = mean(true_vals))
  
  bootstrapping_mse[[i]] <- temporary_df_list[[i]] %>%
    summarise(mse_rf = mean((pred_rf - true_vals)^2),
              mse_xgb = mean((pred_xgb - true_vals)^2),
              mse_ann = mean((pred_ann - true_vals)^2),
              mse_lr = mean((pred_lr - true_vals)^2),
              mse_msbos = mean((pred_msbos - true_vals)^2), 
              mse_gpr = mean((pred_gpr - true_vals)^2))

  bootstrapping_adj_r2[[i]] <- temporary_df_list[[i]] %>%
    summarise(sst = sum((true_vals - mean_true)^2), 
              sse_rf = sum((pred_rf - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_rf = sum((true_vals - pred_rf)^2), 
              adj_r2_rf = 1-((ssr_rf/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1))), 
              
              sse_xgb = sum((pred_xgb - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_xgb = sum((true_vals - pred_xgb)^2), 
              adj_r2_xgb = 1-((ssr_xgb/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1))), 
              
              sse_ann = sum((pred_ann - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_ann = sum((true_vals - pred_ann)^2), 
              adj_r2_ann = 1-((ssr_ann/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1))), 
              
              sse_lr = sum((pred_lr - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_lr = sum((true_vals - pred_lr)^2), 
              adj_r2_lr = 1-((ssr_lr/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1))), 
              
              sse_gpr = sum((pred_gpr - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_gpr = sum((true_vals - pred_gpr)^2), 
              adj_r2_gpr = 1-((ssr_gpr/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1))), 
              
              sse_msbos = sum((pred_msbos - mean_true)^2), 
              ssr_msbos = sum((true_vals - pred_msbos)^2), 
              adj_r2_msbos = 1-((ssr_msbos/(n-k-1))/(sst/(n-1)))) %>%
    select(adj_r2_rf,adj_r2_xgb,adj_r2_ann,adj_r2_lr,adj_r2_msbos, adj_r2_gpr)
  
  bootstrapping_sum_rbc[[i]] <- temporary_df_list[[i]] %>%
    summarise(sum_rbc_rf = sum(pred_rf), 
              sum_rbc_xgb = sum(pred_xgb), 
              sum_rbc_ann = sum(pred_ann), 
              sum_rbc_lr = sum(pred_lr), 
              sum_rbc_msbos = sum(pred_msbos), 
              sum_rbc_gpr = sum(pred_gpr))
}

               names_to = "colnames", 
               values_to = "values") %>%
  mutate(colnames = paste("r", colnames, sep = ""), 
         values = sqrt(values))

Statistical analysis

performance_df1 <- bind_rows(bootstrapping_rmse, bootstrapping_adj_r2, bootstrapping_sum_rbc) %>%
  mutate(colnames = case_when(colnames == "adj_r2_xgb" ~ "adjr2_xgb", 
                              colnames == "adj_r2_rf" ~ "adjr2_rf", 
                              colnames == "adj_r2_ann" ~ "adjr2_ann", 
                              colnames == "adj_r2_gpr" ~ "adjr2_gpr", 
                              colnames == "adj_r2_lr" ~ "adjr2_lr", 
                              colnames == "adj_r2_msbos" ~ "adjr2_msbos", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_xgb" ~ "sumrbc_xgb", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_rf" ~ "sumrbc_rf", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_ann" ~ "sumrbc_ann", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_gpr" ~ "sumrbc_gpr", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_lr" ~ "sumrbc_lr", 
                              colnames == "sum_rbc_msbos" ~ "sumrbc_msbos", 
                              TRUE ~ colnames)) %>%
  separate(colnames, into = c("type", "model")) %>%
  mutate(type = factor(type, levels = c("rmse", "adjr2", "sumrbc")), 
         model = factor(model, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos")))

Verification of normality and homoscedasticity for statistical analysis

ANOVA test and Bonferroni post-hoc test were performed for RBC data, since normality and homoscedasticity are satisfied. Kruskal-Wallis test and Dunn’s post-hoc analysis were conducted for RMSE and adjusted R^2 data, since homoscedasticity were not satisfied.

# bonferroni
stat.test_sumrbc <- performance_df1 %>%
  filter(type == "sumrbc") %>% 
  group_by(type) %>%
  pairwise_t_test(values ~ model, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni") %>%
  filter(p.adj < 0.05/5) %>%
  add_xy_position(x = "model") %>%
  mutate(p.adj = round(p.adj, 3), 
         p.adj = ifelse(p.adj == 0.000, "< 0.001", p.adj)) %>%
  mutate(group1 = factor(group1, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos")), 
         group2 = factor(group2, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos"))) %>%
  arrange(type, group1, group2) %>%
  mutate(y.position = 8300 + 1:13 * 60)

stat.test_rmse_adjr2 <- performance_df1 %>%
  filter(type %in% c("adjr2", "rmse")) %>%
  group_by(type) %>%
  dunn_test(values ~ model, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni") %>%
  filter(p.adj < 0.05/5) %>%
  add_xy_position(x = "model") %>%
  mutate(p.adj = round(p.adj, 3), 
         p.adj = ifelse(p.adj == 0.000, "< 0.001", p.adj)) %>%
  mutate(group1 = factor(group1, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos")), 
         group2 = factor(group2, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos"))) %>%
  arrange(type, group1, group2) %>%
  mutate(y.position = c((3.5+1:10*0.07), (0.47+1:12*0.02)))

## Bland-Altman plot

cut2 = 1


combined_result2_2 <- combined_result1 %>%
  mutate(msbos_gap = true_vals - pred_msbos, 
         rf_gap = true_vals - pred_rf,
         xgb_gap = true_vals - pred_xgb,  
         ann_gap = true_vals - pred_ann, 
         lr_gap = true_vals - pred_lr, 
         gpr_gap = true_vals - pred_gpr) %>%
  mutate(msbos_result = case_when(abs(msbos_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate",
                                  msbos_gap < 0 ~ "pred more",
                                  msbos_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                                  msbos_gap > 0 ~ "pred less",
                                  TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  mutate(rf_result = case_when(abs(rf_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate",
                               rf_gap < 0 ~ "pred more",
                               rf_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                               rf_gap > 0 ~ "pred less",
                               TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  mutate(xgb_result = case_when(abs(xgb_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate", 
                                xgb_gap < 0 ~ "pred more", 
                                xgb_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                                xgb_gap > 0 ~ "pred less", 
                                TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  mutate(ann_result = case_when(abs(ann_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate", 
                                ann_gap < 0 ~ "pred more", 
                                ann_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                                ann_gap > 0 ~ "pred less", 
                                TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  mutate(lr_result = case_when(abs(lr_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate", 
                               lr_gap < 0 ~ "pred more", 
                               lr_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                               lr_gap > 0 ~ "pred less", 
                               TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  mutate(gpr_result = case_when(abs(gpr_gap) <= cut2 ~ "appropriate", 
                               gpr_gap < 0 ~ "pred more", 
                               gpr_gap >= 5 ~ "pred extream less",
                               gpr_gap > 0 ~ "pred less", 
                               TRUE ~ "ELSE")) %>%
  
  mutate(msbos_result = factor(msbos_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less"))) %>%
  mutate(rf_result = factor(rf_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less"))) %>%
  mutate(xgb_result = factor(xgb_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less"))) %>%
  mutate(ann_result = factor(ann_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less"))) %>%
  mutate(lr_result = factor(lr_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less"))) %>%
  mutate(gpr_result = factor(gpr_result, levels = c("pred more", "appropriate", "pred less", "pred extream less")))

Sensitivity analysis

true val == 0

combined_result2_1 <- combined_result1 %>%
  filter(true_vals %in% 0)

ratio = 0.8 # bootstrapping ratio
n = round(nrow(combined_result2_1)*ratio, 0) # nrow
k = 9 # number of input variables

bootstrapping_mse <- list()
bootstrapping_adj_r2 <- list()
bootstrapping_sum_rbc <- list()
temporary_df_list <- list()
for(i in 1: 100) {
  set.seed(i)
  temporary_df_list[[i]] <- combined_result2_1 %>%
    sample_n(n) %>% # bootstraping
    mutate(mean_true = mean(true_vals))
  
  bootstrapping_mse[[i]] <- temporary_df_list[[i]] %>%
    summarise(mse_rf = mean((pred_rf - true_vals)^2),
              mse_xgb = mean((pred_xgb - true_vals)^2),
              mse_ann = mean((pred_ann - true_vals)^2),

  mutate(type = factor(type, levels = c("rmse", "sumrbc")), 
         model = factor(model, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos")))

# ANOVA test and post-hoc analysis
performance_df1 %>%
  group_by(type) %>% 
  anova_test(values ~ model)
## # A tibble: 2 × 8
##   type   Effect   DFn   DFd      F         p `p<.05`   ges
## * <fct>  <chr>  <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl>     <dbl> <chr>   <dbl>
## 1 rmse   model      5   594   84.1 9.58e- 67 *       0.414
## 2 sumrbc model      5   594 1245.  5.55e-312 *       0.913
stat.test <- performance_df1 %>%
  group_by(type) %>%
  pairwise_t_test(values ~ model, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni") %>%
  filter(p.adj < 0.05/5) %>%
  add_xy_position(x = "model") %>%
  mutate(p.adj = round(p.adj, 3),
         p.adj = ifelse(p.adj == 0.000, "< 0.001", p.adj)) %>%
  mutate(group1 = factor(group1, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos")),
         group2 = factor(group2, levels = c("xgb", "rf", "ann", "gpr", "lr", "msbos"))) %>%
  arrange(type, group1, group2) %>%
  mutate(y.position = c(c(3.8+1:7*0.07), c(7200 + 1:14 * 55)))
